timeline.body:
Can the case of `target == player && opponent != null && opponent != lastOpponent` ever happen? You have 4 different paths here:

1) `target == player && opponent == null`
2) `target == player && opponent != null && opponent != lastOpponent` <-- does this happen?
3) `target != player && source == lastOpponent && target == player ...` obviously this cannot happen
4) `target != player && source == lastOpponent && opponent != lastOpponent`

I think this can't happen because it would require something to attack you while you were attacking something that also wasn't your opponent. And I don't think you can be attacking something which isn't your opponent.

If so, this can just be split I think into two separate ifs

```java
if (target == player && opponent == null) {
// Case of something attacking you when you aren't in combat
}
else if (source == lastOpponent && opponent != lastOpponent) {
// Case of something attacking you switching off while you are not attacking it
}
```

